description:
Non material minor amendment of planning permission re P100557 dated 7 February 2011 which extended the time limit for planning permission ref: P072654 dated 28.01.08. The application is for the "Development of 22-24 Highbury Grove involving the demolition of existing buildings (except 24 Highbury Grove) and construction of new buildings for commercial use (Use Class B1) and 72 residential units of flats and townhouses. The buildings range from three to five storeys."  The amendments involve; 
-	changes to the fenestration on the western elevation of Block B;
-	an additional balcony and the extension of an existing balcony on the western elevation of Block B;
-	alterations to the fenestration on the northern elevation of Block A;
-	alterations to the treatment at roof level along the northern elevation of Block B;
-	an additional door at 3rd floor level and changes to the fenestration on the northern elevation of Block B;
-	additional balconies on the eastern elevation of Block B;
